    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\na spot like this:\r\n\r\n![ceb6f12c-49bd-11ef-9e05-54b203702c9c](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/76e5d6b0-6b36-4c8d-aa97-5c11f5bc5c63)\r\n\r\nwhich will not remain long, yet `:redraw` and `:redraw!` can not clear it.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n* test.lua\r\n```\r\n------\r\n------\r\n\r\nlocal api = vim.api\r\n\r\nlocal text = \"üÖ∞Ô∏è\"\r\n\r\nlocal bufnr = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\napi.nvim_buf_set_lines(bufnr, 0, -1, false, { text })\r\n\r\nlocal winid = api.nvim_open_win(bufnr, false, {\r\n  relative = \"editor\",\r\n  row = 1,\r\n  col = 1,\r\n  width = api.nvim_strwidth(text),\r\n  height = 1,\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.print(\"winid\", winid)\r\nvim.schedule(function() api.nvim_win_set_config(winid, { hide = true }) end)\r\n```\r\n* `$ nvim --clean -u NONE test.lua`\r\n* `:so`\r\n* see the white spot\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nnothing of a floatwin will be left when it's being hidden.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nnvim 0.10\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\narchlinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nst 0.9.2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nst-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\npacman",
